runs.comm: short and whipped into the leg side
140 kph, good channel outside off and allowed through to keeper
whipped off his hip to short fine leg
full and driven past mid on for four
driven to extra cover
uses the pace and plays to point
half volley on leg stump and worked to deep square leg
shortish and mistimed pull to mid on
half volley and Warner lays into it, times is beautifully over long off for six
good length but too much width and he slashes over backward square for four
too wide of off stump
full and offers width and slays it over point for four
full and driven to point where Guptill fields and throws at the stumps but misses, he was home anyway
yorker played to mid on
full from Bond and Warner hits through the line, clearing the front leg out of the way and it goes over mid off for four
bumper from Bond and Warner hooks it high off the top edge, Southee moves back from short fine leg and takes a good catch over his shoulder. That one had snow on it coming down
yorker played back to the bowler
good length and punched to backward point
back of a length and pushed into the off side for a quick single
fuller from Southee and Haddin drives sweetly back past the bowler for four straight down the ground
full again but a better length and Haddin drives off the inside half of the bat to mid wicket
good channel from Southee and Clarke wants to have a look and pushes into the off side
shortish from Southee and Clarke pulls neatly over square leg for four
back of a length and Clarke plays nicely with soft hands into the off side for a quick single
half volley outside off and driven to cover
back of a length and Clarke plays it late, hitting it straight into the ground to backward point
fuller and square driven to point
slower ball is full and driven to cover
146 kph, back of a length and Haddin is beaten by a good delivery outside off
Haddin psuhes into the off side and Nathan McCullum hits from point at the bowlers' end but Haddin is home safe
fullish length and Clarke comes forward and pushes to mid off for a single
Oram attacks the stumps and Clarke plays to mid wicket
slower ball and Clarke walks across his stumps and whips it behind square and it runs away for four
good length from Oram and Clarke is back and defending along the pitch
dropped back of a length from Oram and Clarke pulls in the air towards mid on and Southee moves well, sticks out his right hand and it hits him in the wrist and it goes down. Not a bad effort
gives himself room and cuts to point
fraction too short and pulled for half a dozen into the stands. That's gone 30 rows back!
back of a length and played with soft hands to backward point
comes down the track and driven on the up to long off
flatter and Haddin attempts a cut, it takes a bottom edge and runs fine for four
back of a length and he pushes to cover where Guptill dives and gets a hand to it
short and punched to cover where Nathan Mc dives to prevent the scoring to just the single
short and cut to deep point
good length but Haddin stands and delivers over straight mid wicket for half a dozen
half volley driven to long off
yorker driven off the inside half of the bat to mid wicket
droppedfull and wide and Haddin goes down on one knee and square drives to Guptill at deep point, he dives and yorks himself and can't hold onto it
Oram oversteps and bowls a yorker which Clarke plays to mid wicket
Haddin tries to hit over long on but it's a good yorker and he plays onto his stumps but he's not out as it was a free-hit
yorker dug out to long off, they look for a couple but can't get back
good length he uses his feet and plays back to the bowler
tossed up and Haddin drives off the inside edge to mid wicket and they run well to take two
flat and Haddin goes back and late cuts to short third man
flatter again but straighter this time and he pushes into the off side
fuller ad Haddin pushes to long on
flat again and driven off the back foot to deep cover
half volley and driven to extra cover, Vettori throws at the stumps but misses
half volley driven to long off
full again and driven to Vettori at extra cover, it hits a bump in the outfield and hits Vettori in the neck as he dives to stop it
yorker just wide of off stump and Haddin plays it late, opens the face and it runs fine of short third man
another yorker just wide of off and he plays late again but right out of the middle and straight to Franklin at short third man
Oram oversteps again and bowls a yorker which Haddin digs out to Nathan Mc at point
half volley and he can't get underneath it and drivesalong the deck to long off
tossed up and driven into the off side where Vettori fields well
quicker and angled into the leg stump and he whips it to deep square leg
Haddin walks across his stumps and picks it up from off stump and drop kicks it over square leg for six
angled into the pads and worked into the leg side
tossed up and Clarke uses his feet and drives to long on
angled into the pads and clipped through the leg side to the sweeper
short and pulled in the air out to deep mid wicket where Ingram takes a good catch low down
length delivery and Clarke plays it late to short third man
Franklin oversteps and guided to short third man
full and driven in the air to Hopkins at long off
yorker played into the leg side
half volley driven back to the bowler
half volley, a fraction wider this time and Hussey drives gorgeously through the covers for four
Clarke uses his feet and tries to slog it over cow corner, he gets a bottom edge and it runs to short fine leg
uses his feet and drives to long on
watches it longer this time and slog sweeps over straight mid wicket for four
uses his feet and Clarke gets to it on the half volley and hits it straight over the bowlers' head for half a dozen
Nathan Mc comes around the wicket and Clarke gives himself room and edges fine past Hopkins for four
tossed up and worked into the leg side
gives himself room and tries to play through the off side but it takes him on the hip and drops into the leg side
full and hammered thrugh cover for four, superb timing
slower ball from Franklin and Hussey tries to go over mid wicket but misses and he's cleaned out
full and he tries to use the pace and plays to Nathan Mc at backward point, he looks for a single but can't get it
full outside off, White looks to drive but misses
angled into the pads and White drives to long on
gives himself room and launches half a dozen over extra cover, what a stroke
slower this time, that's gutsy from Vettori, and he works it to long on
flatter and driven to deep point off the back foot
backs away to leg again and White launches it over wide long off for six more. Glorious shot!

droppedWhite gives himself room again and hits over extra cover where Nathan Mc jumps high into the air on the ropes and puts it down as he striggles to stay inside the perimeter. Great effort but that goes down as a dropped catch unfortunately
chipped over the bowler to long on
worked through the leg side to the sweeper
low full toss and he cross-bats it straight down the gound for four
slower ball and he mistimes the square drive through mid off to the man on the fence
walks across to the off side and whips it through the leg side to the sweeper in front of square
Franklin bowls a decent length but White just leans back and heaves it over long off for six more. This kid can really play
low full toss and White hammers it over extra cover for four more. That is a crucial over in the context of the match
slower short ball and he cuts on the bounce to deep point
bumper from Bond and hite goes inside the line. It was close to a wide for being too high
Bond goes around the wicket and bowls straight into White's arc and he clubs it over square leg for a maximum. He did it with such ease
angled into the hip and clipped to the leg side sweeper
gives himself just enough room to hit over cover for four. That's a very good stroke
full and at the stumps and mistimed drive into the leg side
Southee hits the block hole and Clarke drives to cover
Southee goes full again and White can only dig it out to long on
yorker dug out to deep mid wicket
impeccable length again as he hist the hole and he digs it out to long off
yorker length again and Clarke comes down the track and gets to it on the full but can only dig it out to long off
the best yorker of the over and White digs it out into the off side
Oram is full, it's not quite yorker length and White clubs it to long on for a single
yorker dug out into the off side, Oram dives, picks it up and throws it to Hopkins who fumbles and that may well have been run out had he held onto it
full but not full enough and White drives in the air through long on for four
low full toss and White drives it straight back past the bowler for four
yorker length but well wide off off stump
just misses yorker length and White launches it high, long and handsome over long on for another maximum. Exactly what Australia needed
yorker dug out to long on, good finish
yorker again, dug out to long on and they can only take the single
Clarke moves across to the off side and Southee follows him and Clarke whips it into the leg side to the sweeper
full and clubbed down the ground and Brendon Mc msfields in the deep and they take a tight second
full and he just misses the yorker, White cracks it straight, just past Southee's head for four, amazing power!
yorker length driven to long on and Brendon Mc does well to prevent the second. If it's a tie it will go down to a Super Over! The scenes are electric here.

Clarke moves forward, gets to it on the full and clubs it to long on, Nathan Mc dives to save the boundary and parries it, the batsmen come back for the third but Clarke is well short and we are going to a Super Over! What a match folks. This is sensational stuff!
